how_to_use: Apply to clean, damp hair. Leave on for 3-20 minutes, depending on desired effect. Rinse thoroughly. Use as needed, whenever you want a color boost and to add extra shine. Lasts up to ten shampoos. All Gloss+ shades can be mixed with Sheer to create your ideal Gloss+ shade.

reviews.headline: Didn't Do Anything
reviews.comments: I had high hopes for this gloss as the reviews/articles said it would add shine and color. Sadly disappointed on both fronts and product was returned.

reviews.headline: Fan of this gloss!
reviews.comments: I love the clear / sheer gloss and the black one! I use the clear instead of my conditioner, and I use the black one to temporarily cover my gray sprouts and all over rich color! I leave the clear one on for 5 minutes if I'm in a rush but otherwise I leave both in for 15 minutes.

reviews.headline: Will NOT Buy Again
reviews.comments: This product left my hair BLOTCHY as it did with other users. I Always read and follow instructions. Have used several similar products but never had results like this. Product was also so thick you could not pump it.  Can't recommend to anyone. Maybe a bad batch? Returning.

reviews.headline: Not for me
reviews.comments: The two times I used DP Hue (one copper one auburn) the color on my hair was way off. I had brown hair with some strands of blonde poking through and using the copper I ended up with Maniac Panic bright red, which I was not expecting and slightly darker red with auburn. Could be my start point but these did NOT work for me.

reviews.headline: Super impressed!
reviews.comments: I am writing this after using this product because I am surprised at so many negative comments.  I absolutely LOVED this product. I have naturally dirty blonde hair with light blonde highlights‚Ä¶. The golden blonde shade gave my hair life when it was dull‚Ä¶..it was unbelievably soft after using and looked like I just got fresh color.  I made sure to wash and conditioner my hair first, as for a smell‚Ä¶ I didn't notice anything and didn't need to use too much to cover my long hair.  I would definitely recommend!!!

reviews.headline: Splotchy Mess :-(
reviews.comments: Does NOT go on evenly. It picks up darker in different parts of the hair! If you have highlights hair and it's more dry in the highlights area- it will pick up very dark in those areas of highlights. My hair was very highlights light in the front and with this product now those highlights areas are SO dark- so dark compared to the rest. I do not like what this did to my hair sad :-(

reviews.headline: Absolutely will keep buying!
reviews.comments: I have a blonde balayage/full highlights. My natural hair color is light/medium brown with golden tips, like naturally. Ever since I started dyibg my hair a few years ago, I have never seen my virgin hair color again. With the Dark Blonde tone it quite literally took my hair back to how it looked when I was like 5 years old. Which I love, I also love that its temporary, and it made my hair super super shiny so I did not have to damage it.

reviews.headline: ... Going with a big old NO on this one!
reviews.comments: THE WRAP UP: Over-promised, under-delivered! I should have known better by the bottle alone. Feels like a low effort product put out to deceive people into thinking it was a big hair fix. It did nothing for my hair! Its conditioner at the end of the day and not even a decent moisturizing conditioner at that. Money grab product 100%

reviews.headline: Smell is terrible
reviews.comments: Truly one of the worst smelling products I've ever used. I ended up rinsing it out after only a few minutes. It also is difficult to distribute evenly.

reviews.headline: Idk what this is supposed to do
reviews.comments: I genuinely don't know what this product was supposed to do. Or what it thought it was supposed to do. I have used it 3 times in 1.5 months: the bottle is much smaller than I thought it would be and you have to use a lot of product to ensure proper coverage. It also did not moisturize my hair, I actually think it may have stripped moisture and shine from my hair pre-use. There was no tint to this gloss. None. The product itself is tinted but it left absolutley nothing in my hair. I love this product in theory, but in practice, it's just more overpriced goo that doesn't do what it claims to do.

reviews.headline: *WISH* this worked!
reviews.comments: The idea of this sounded good, but it did not deliver. No *SHINE* and no added TONE at all. Like everyone else here is saying- Yes, the smell is AWFUL and OVERWHELMING. All in all- a terrible experience, waste of time, and waste of money.

reviews.headline: CONFUSED...
reviews.comments: It didn't help to gloss my hair. Just left a reddish tone all over. In the natural light my brown  hair looks red now. Help?

reviews.headline: Does not go on evenly unfortunately!
reviews.comments: I was hoping this product would gloss/tone my six month old streaks because I was tired of the ombre effect I had going on, but this left my ends looking very spotty and uneven. The ends now look darker than my roots and almost like a cheetah spots and it's very inconsistent. The front pieces framing my face turned the darkest which is what is so noticeable. I spent more on the bottle than I would have spent in the salon and now I won't use the rest of the bottle. Afraid to show my stylist at the salon so I am hoping it fades in the next few weeks.

reviews.headline: Love!!
reviews.comments: How have I gone this long without this?! Love love love how shiny and soft it made my hair ü•πü•π will definitely repurchase once I finish this bottle ‚ù§Ô∏è

reviews.headline: A must have between color application
reviews.comments: Easy to use. Great conditioner and adds a ton of shine. I've been using it for the last 3 years, every 10 to 15 days between application.

reviews.headline: Did Nothing
reviews.comments: Got the carmel gloss shade and it did nothing on my hair and I have blonde hair so it should hvae pi ked up something.

reviews.headline: Love it, Works for me!
reviews.comments: I bought the copper and dark brown to maintain my calico hair between salon visits. It smoothed out my hair and made it soft. It added some shine. I definitely noticed a difference with the copper color depositing and my hair looks refreshed! I like that it comes in a pump bottle so its easy to use and no mixing! This will last me a while since the brown and copper are small sections. Only con I can think of is the smell, but it just smells like any other hair dye to me.

reviews.headline: Did nothing
reviews.comments: Strawberry did nothing at all. Left it on for full 20 minutes. The mask got darker over time but washed out and hair color exactlt the same.

reviews.headline: I'm never buy again from
reviews.comments: Im never buy again from  Ulta very poor product my hair same colour nothing change

reviews.headline: Hair is nice and soft. Can't tell the difference in color.
reviews.comments: I got the black dye to make my dark brown hair extra darker. It seems like an alright product and it may have some potential but it feels like it didn't do much of a difference in the change of color. I could have done this wrong but I don't know for sure. This was my first time dying my hair on my own so in the product's defense, I'm a complete rookie in hair coloring. Maybe I'll leave it in longer than 20 minutes the next time I use it. I don't plan on giving up on this though. It's a learning experience and I gave it a shot, to say the least. The positive is that it made my hair super soft so I can't complain about that. It also covered up some of the white hairs I have growing too so I'm sure it did something. I just can't tell with the natural dark brown hair is all. The smell is a little strange too but it doesn't bother me all that much.

faceoff_positive.comments: I really hesitated to buy this because of the price and I wasn't sure how it would work but Ulta has such a libral return policy I thought I would try it. I used this when my hair had a lot of gray roots and I should have been using a box color like I usually do so this was a pretty tough test of the product. I washed my hair first and then applied the "stain". I used a lot it seemed and concentrated on my most gray areas. I left it in 2 hours because I wanted maximum color. My hands were stained with the warm brown color and did not come clean with soap and water. I used sink cleaner with bleach and it took the stain right off. I rinsed the product out after 2 hours (cleaned my house while it was processing), applied my normal stying products and blow dried my hair. My hair is very thick and coarse and does not usually hold color well. My hair came out feeling very silky and soft. I could tell a difference in color too. My hair seemed more of a rich tone. I would say this product is like a deep conditioner with a color stain. It did not totally cover my gray but blended it pretty well. Not sure how long it will last as I just used this product.
faceoff_positive.headline: Seems to work

faceoff_negative.comments: Discovered this at Ulta by accident.  I was excited about this product. I'm getting tired of root touch ups every 2 weeks. Well it did nothing. I left it on for 40 mins. As I was waiting, it looked like my roots were turning golden brown. I needed darker, but I would have been fine with it.  Washed it out and was really disappointed. Did NOTHING!!! Returning!!!
faceoff_negative.headline: Does not work!
